	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="To trigger ROTHE ARE AFRAID, NOT MET&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game.&#xD;&#xA;2. Use Recon command: &quot;loadlevel WLD_Main_A&quot;&#xD;&#xA;3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster.&#xD;&#xA;4. Talk with Morgya.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;To trigger ROTHE ARE AFRAID, MET&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game.&#xD;&#xA;2. Use Recon command: &quot;loadlevel WLD_Main_A&quot;&#xD;&#xA;3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster.&#xD;&#xA;4. Talk with Morgya.&#xD;&#xA;5. Talk to Morgya again.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;To trigger ROTHE ARE DEAD&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game.&#xD;&#xA;2. Use Recon command: &quot;loadlevel WLD_Main_A&quot;&#xD;&#xA;3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster.&#xD;&#xA;4. Use Recon command: &quot;SetGlobalOsirisFlag UND_FearfulRothe_State_RotheAreDead&quot;&#xD;&#xA;5. Talk with Morgya.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;To trigger ROTHE CALM, RUBBLE STILL THERE&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game.&#xD;&#xA;2. Use Recon command: &quot;loadlevel WLD_Main_A&quot;&#xD;&#xA;3. goto -677.266; 13.025; 441.9 and leave the dialog with herdmaster&#xD;&#xA;4. Use Recon command: &quot;addDebugSpell Shout_SpeakWithAnimals&quot; and &quot;infiniteAp&quot;&#xD;&#xA;5. Talk with the Rothe in front of the herdmaster and convince it to attack the rubble.&#xD;&#xA;6. Rapidly talk with Morgya while rubbles are still up.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;To trigger ROTHE CALM, RUBBLE REMOVED&#xD;&#xA;..." />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="9" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="A coarse and unempathetic duergar, one of three guarding some Deep Rothe (beasts of burden currently being used to clear rubble).&#xD;&#xA;Different reactions if:&#xD;&#xA;- animals are panicking;&#xD;&#xA;- animals are calm;&#xD;&#xA;- animals are dead (doesn't matter how);" />
